Hello Davide,IE, one of the leading higher education institutions in the world, is pleased to invite you to a unique Executive Breakfast "The Future of Finance in the Era of 4IR" in Milan.Much has been talked about Industrial Revolutions that has taken place since the 18th century but not so much about Finance Revolutions. Yes, clearly Industrial Revolutions had to be funded and clearly the way money arrived to make possible those revolutions has changed dramatically.First, Second and Third Industrial revolutions have seen energy, industries and communications to change dramatically. At the same time finance has evolved from merchant Banks to Capital Markets and Structured Finance. Fourth industrial revolution is said to bring renewable energy definitely together with internet of things, biotechnology and Artificial Intelligence. Regarding Finance, clearly Fintech is going to help change our lives.AgendaFriday, March 23, 2018 at 09:00 hrs.Executive Breakfast "The Future of Finance in the Era of 4IR"NH Milano Touring Via Iginio Ugo Tarchetti 2, 20121 Milan.About the speakerWith 8 years of teaching experience at IE and more than 20 at other institutions, Professor Rafael Martins de Lima is an expert in Finance focusing on Financial Markets, Risk Management and Financial Management. Professionally, he started working developing Artificial intelligence systems for Procter & Gamble, but very soon he switched his career to Management and Banking, firstly at McKinsey & Company as a consultant, following at Amadeus as Business Development Manager and after at Banco Santander.There, he reached the level of Managing Director (Subdirector General Adjunto) working in America, Europe and Africa in areas such as Corporate Finance, Capital Markets, Consumer Finance and Risk Management. Currently he runs Hera W2R (Waste to Resource), company that works in the fields of Renewable Energy and Carbon Finance. His dual education on Finance and Engineering combined with his experience in consulting, banking and industry makes him a deep academic with a direct to the point view on real life practice.Please confirm your attendance as places are limited.We look forward to meeting you soon!Best regards,Andrea CoppolaDirector IE Office Italy, Balkans, San Marino, Vatican CityAndrea.Coppola@ie.edu

Ciao Davide,  figo.  Finalmente anche tu ti sei deciso a prendere una decisione saggia.  Per quanto riguarda lo stipendio, considera he:  - prezzo medio del cibo al supermercato √® del 30% in piu rispetto all'italia (media sugli stessi prodotti)  - affitto per 45/50 mq in zona semicentrale di zurigo stai sui 2500 franchi al mese  - biglietto base per il tram √® 4.2 franchi (quello che a milano in metro costa 1.5 ‚Ç¨)   Inoltre considera che con il tuo stipendio netto devi pagare:  - fondo pensione (circa 300 franchi al mese) che ti vengono tolti direttamente dal cedolino  - assicurazione sanitaria (a meno che non te la dia la banca come benefit) che, nella versine base base come la mia ti costa sui 250-300 franchi al mese.
